		"description": "Defining only a \"special\" color state ({{backgroundFocusedColor}}, {{backgroudDisabledColor}} or {{backgroundSelectedColor}}) without the default {{backgroundColor}} for a View results in a view with a transparent background.\r\n\r\nThis is sort of a \"partial regression\" meaning that 7.5.0 exposed it through the {{backgroundDisabledColor}} fix, but it was the same for the other two properties before that.\r\n\r\nsample:\r\n{code:java}\r\nvar win = Ti.UI.createWindow(),\r\n    button = Ti.UI.createButton({\r\n        backgroundSelectedColor: 'red',\r\n        title: 'Button',\r\n        width: 100,\r\n        height: 100\r\n    });\r\n\r\nwin.add(button);\r\nwin.open();\r\n{code}\r\n",
		"attachment": [],
		"flagged": false,
		"summary": "Android: setting one of the color states may break the default background",
